<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="237" pageId="9" pageNumber="236" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,2021]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1960,1985]" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">Etymology</emphasis>
. This new species is named after Jean-Yves Gallard, in recognition of his contribution in the taxonomy of the 
<taxonomicName box="[341,464,1996,2021]" class="Insecta" family="Riodinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Riodinidae</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[533,702,1996,2021]" name="French Guiana" pageId="9" pageNumber="236">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,305,151,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Ethology</emphasis>
. In 
<number box="[353,408,152,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="2011.0">2011</number>
a single male was collected in the third day of sampling at the hilltop while resting on a liana leaf, about five meters from the ground around 
<number box="[747,775,188,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="15.0">15</number>
: 
<number box="[779,811,188,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="30.0">30</number>
h. The female here illustrated was collected in the same day, while flying slowly about one meter from the ground, close to the Moa River, around 
<number box="[1192,1221,223,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="16.0">16</number>
: 
<number box="[1225,1257,223,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="30.0">30</number>
h. The 
<typeStatus box="[1338,1436,223,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected in 
<number box="[338,394,260,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="2014.0">2014</number>
flying with specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Hall &amp; Willmott, 1995" authorityName="Hall &amp; Willmott" authorityYear="1995" box="[686,1047,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="celata">
<emphasis box="[686,786,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">A. celata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[793,1047,260,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1995) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, with descriptions of five new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 6, 136 - 143." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hall &amp; Willmott, 
<number box="[991,1047,260,285]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="1995.0">1995</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
about two meters from the ground around 
<number box="[236,264,295,320]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="18.0">18</number>
:00h.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="237" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,332,357]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Distribution</emphasis>
. This uncommon species is currently known only from two males collected in the north region of the 
<collectionCode box="[191,265,368,392]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">PNSD</collectionCode>
, northwest of Acre, on the border between 
<collectingCountry box="[744,812,367,392]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[866,920,368,391]" name="Peru" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and from a 
<typeStatus box="[1057,1154,368,392]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">paratype</typeStatus>
collected near to 
<taxonomicName authority="Cayenne" authorityName="Cayenne" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Regina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Régina, Cayenne</taxonomicName>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[263,433,404,429]" name="French Guiana" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="237" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,439,464]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Brevignon" box="[344,878,439,464]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard (
<number box="[604,665,439,464]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="1995.0">1995</number>
: 
<number box="[678,782,439,464]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="404.405">404, 405</number>
: fig. 
<number box="[842,869,440,464]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="11.0">11</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
illustrate a male and a female specimen, therein identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[300,447,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amalfreda">
<emphasis box="[300,447,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">A. amalfreda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Staudinger, [
<number box="[610,674,476,500]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="1887.0">1887</number>
]). As noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hall" box="[852,1127,476,501]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" refString="Hall, J. P. W. &amp; Willmott, K. R. (1995) Notes on the genus Argyrogrammana, with descriptions of five new species (Lepidoptera: Riodinidae). Tropical Lepidoptera, 6, 136 - 143." type="journal article" year="1995">
Hall &amp; Willmott (
<number box="[1058,1118,476,501]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the male specimen differs significantly from Staudinger’s [
<number box="[514,575,512,536]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="1887.0">1887</number>
] 
<typeStatus box="[589,641,512,536]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">type</typeStatus>
. The male specimen in fact represents a new species, here described as 
<taxonomicName box="[151,276,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallardi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,276,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">A. gallardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[287,381,548,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[287,374,548,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
The female specimen illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brevignon" box="[817,1213,548,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" refString="Brevignon, C. &amp; Gallard, J. - Y. (1995) Contribuition a l'etude des Riodinidae de Guyane Francaise. Le genre Argyrogrammana Strand, 1932. Lambillionea, 95, 393 - 406." type="journal article" year="1995">
Brévignon &amp; Gallard (
<number box="[1085,1146,548,573]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="1995.0">1995</number>
: 
<number box="[1161,1204,548,572]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="394.0">394</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
is apparently nonconspecific with the male. The female collected in 
<number box="[717,772,584,608]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="2011.0">2011</number>
at the same day and near the place where the male 
<typeStatus box="[1340,1436,584,608]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">paratype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectionCode box="[212,284,620,644]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">PNSD</collectionCode>
was collected is here tentatively matched with this species due to its black spots pattern of both wings similar to males. Nevertheless, considering the great dimorphism found in almost all species of the genus and that some 
<taxonomicName box="[221,419,692,715]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[221,419,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">Argyrogrammana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are known only from one of the sexes, we chose a conservative action do not including this female in the 
<typeStatus box="[474,522,728,752]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">type</typeStatus>
series of 
<taxonomicName box="[636,758,727,752]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gallardi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[636,758,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">A. gallardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[767,858,727,752]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[767,858,727,752]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
. Despite the spots pattern on the wings, similar to species from “ 
<taxonomicName box="[313,374,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stilbe">
<emphasis box="[313,374,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">stilbe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex”, its genitalia morphology (
<figureCitation box="[795,877,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 63 – 66" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1830,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,253,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,253,1809]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 63 – 66. Female genitalia of species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 63. A. gallardi sp. nov. (tentatively determination). 64. A. willmotti, sp. nov. allotype. 65. A. iracyi. 66. A. saulensis tunari comb. nov. Top to bottom lateral view of papila analis and ventral view of sterigma and bursae copulatrix. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233294/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
Fig. 
<number box="[848,877,764,789]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="63.0">63</number>
</figureCitation>
) has several differential features of those females belonging to “ 
<taxonomicName box="[312,372,799,824]" class="Insecta" family="Lycaenidae" genus="Argyrogrammana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stilbe">
<emphasis box="[312,372,799,824]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">stilbe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex” found at the 
<collectionCode box="[639,710,800,824]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">PNSD</collectionCode>
(
<figureCitation box="[726,857,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 63 – 66" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1830,1852]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,253,1808]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,253,1809]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 63 – 66. Female genitalia of species of Argyrogrammana collected at the PNSD. 63. A. gallardi sp. nov. (tentatively determination). 64. A. willmotti, sp. nov. allotype. 65. A. iracyi. 66. A. saulensis tunari comb. nov. Top to bottom lateral view of papila analis and ventral view of sterigma and bursae copulatrix. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/233294/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="237">
Figs 
<number box="[783,857,799,824]" pageId="10" pageNumber="237" value="65.0" valueMax="66.0" valueMin="64.0">64–66</number>
</figureCitation>
), as the rounded lamella ante and postvaginalis and signa widely nonaligned.
</paragraph>
